      "instruction": "Drain and rinse beans."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Bring to a boil with chicken stock, water, and coconut cream."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 1 1/2-2 hours or until beans are tender and creamy."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the thyme, allspice, scallion, onion, garlic, scotch bonnet, brown sugar, uncooked rice, salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Check the level of liquid over the rice and make sure there is at least one inch of liquid (if not, you may add water or broth to cover)."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20-30 minutes or until rice is tender."
    },
    {
